Commissioners were commonly appointed to direct the work of the ayrimensores‚ which was carried out with scrupulous nicety on traditional principles, and to assign the allotments‚ the size of which was determined by the senate or commonS. Polyb. 111. 40 says that there were 6000 colonists in each, and that they were directed to be on the spot within 30 days, Note the anomaly of the form triumviri, duumviri, which grew probably out of the use of the singular triumvir, as one of a board of three.

Mutina was itself a Roman colony, Polyb. 111. 40, though Livy states that it was colonized with Parma in 184 Β. c. (L. xxxm. 55). That the Romans chose well the sites of their colonies is illustrated by the importance of the towns of Modena, Piacenza and Cremona.
